The local CPF says the 15-year-old boy was sitting alongside a road when he was approached by two alleged gangsters who shot him. CAPE TOWN - Police are still hunting for two suspects for the killing of a teenager in Hanover Park.The local Community Policing Forum says the 15-year-old boy was sitting alongside a road after walking his sister to school on Thursday morning. He was then approached by two alleged gangsters who shot him.The CPF s Ebrahim Abrahams said: They were wearing school uniform and apparently they are known to some of the children who were walking [on that street], but the children didn t know that they had guns on them. (Edited by Winnie Theletsane)